The paper deals with the parameterized complexity of the Node Multiway Cut problem, which is a graph problem. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of algorithms and their running times, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. The problem of Multiway Cut is related to graph theory and combinatorial optimization, which makes cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) possible sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper involves the study of LP-relaxations, which is a topic in optimization and linear programming, and could place it in the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category.
